The paper discusses spectrum sensing techniques for cognitive radio systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and computer networks and communications (cs.CR). The paper also analyzes the effect of spectral features on sensing performance, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) or multimedia (cs.MM).
